"title": "1130: God, sovereignty of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "1130",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The fact that God is free and able to do all that he wills; that he reigns over all creation and that his will is the final cause of all things. This is often expressed in the language of kingship.</p>\n<h2>God is free to do all he wills</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps135:6\">PSA 135:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps115:3\">PSA 115:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa46:10\">ISA 46:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:19-Rom9:21\">ROM 9:19–9:21</a></p>\n<h2>God is able to do whatever he wills</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:37\">LUK 1:37</a></strong> <em>Gabriel speaking to Mary.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:2\">JOB 42:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:26\">MAT 19:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:20\">EPH 3:20</a></p>\n<h2>God cannot be successfully opposed</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job42:2\">JOB 42:2</a></strong> <em>From Job's prayer of submission and repentance.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:10\">1SA 2:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr20:6\">2CH 20:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job9:12\">JOB 9:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl7:13\">ECC 7:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:13\">ISA 43:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:9-Isa45:10\">ISA 45:9–45:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:39\">ACT 5:39</a></p>\n<h2>God rules and reigns</h2>\n<h3>He is King</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps29:10\">PSA 29:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:31\">1CH 16:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps47:2\">PSA 47:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:5\">ISA 6:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa43:15\">ISA 43:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:7\">JER 10:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:10\">JER 10:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech14:9\">ZEC 14:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:17\">1TI 1:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim6:15\">1TI 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev15:3\">REV 15:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev19:6\">REV 19:6</a></p>\n<h3>He is Lord of heaven and earth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut4:39\">DEU 4:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:3\">GEN 24:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:14\">DEU 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh2:11\">JOS 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:11\">1CH 29:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:6\">NEH 9:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps121:2\">PSA 121:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps134:3\">PSA 134:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:21\">LUK 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:24\">ACT 17:24</a></p>\n<h3>His throne is a symbol of his sovereignty</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod17:16\">EXO 17:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps45:6\">PSA 45:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:2\">PSA 93:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps123:1\">PSA 123:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:1\">ISA 6:1</a> <em>Isaiah's commission</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa66:1\">ISA 66:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer49:38\">JER 49:38</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam5:19\">LAM 5:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:26\">EZK 1:26</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:9\">DAN 7:9</a> <em>Daniel's dream</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:34\">MAT 5:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:28\">MAT 19:28</a> <em>Jesus Christ teaches his disciples about things to come</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts7:49\">ACT 7:49</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:8\">HEB 1:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:1\">HEB 8:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb12:2\">HEB 12:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:2\">REV 4:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev20:11\">REV 20:11</a></p>\n<h2>God's sovereignty extends over all things</h2>\n<h3>He is sovereign over creation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:11\">REV 4:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps93:1\">PSA 93:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa40:22\">ISA 40:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:18-Isa41:19\">ISA 41:18–41:19</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign over human life</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:12\">1CH 29:12</a></strong> <em>Part of David's prayer on the occasion of gifts being brought to the temple.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr25:8\">2CH 25:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:51-Luke1:53\">LUK 1:51–1:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:21\">ACT 18:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas4:15\">JAS 4:15</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign over the minutest details of life</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:29-Matt10:30\">MAT 10:29–10:30</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:6-Luke12:7\">LUK 12:6–12:7</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign in electing his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:11\">EPH 1:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:29\">ROM 8:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:11\">ROM 9:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:18\">ROM 9:18</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign in the life and salvation of his people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:6\">JER 18:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor12:11\">1CO 12:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:13\">PHP 2:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:18\">JAS 1:18</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign over the sufferings of believers</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:29\">PHP 1:29</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:17\">1PE 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>He is sovereign over world history</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:1\">PRO 21:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod9:16\">EXO 9:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps22:28\">PSA 22:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:7-Jer18:10\">JER 18:7–18:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan4:35\">DAN 4:35</a></p>\n<h2>God is sovereign over all other gods and over demonic forces</h2>\n<h3>God is supreme over all gods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:3\">PSA 95:3</a></strong> <em>“gods” are part of the created order and subject to God's sovereignty.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod18:11\">EXO 18:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:17\">DEU 10:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:26\">1CH 16:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps96:5\">PSA 96:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:47\">DAN 2:47</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:16\">COL 1:16</a></p>\n<h3>Satan is defeated through God's sovereign purposes at work in Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:15\">COL 2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John12:31\">JHN 12:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom16:20\">ROM 16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess2:8\">2TH 2:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet2:4\">2PE 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:8\">1JN 3:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jude1:6\">JUD 1:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev12:7-Rev12:10\">REV 12:7–12:10</a></p>",
